text: Kenlyn Gonsalves (born March 16, 1976) is a Saint Vincent and the Grenadines former international footballer, who played as a striker. == Biography == Gonsalves played for the Saint Vincent and the Grenadines national football team between 1995 and 2005. Kenlyn Gonsalves at national-football-teams.com He took part in the 1996 Gold Cup in the United States. He played in one game in the competition, against Mexico. He also took part in 1998 FIFA World Cup qualification, 2002 FIFA World Cup qualification, and 2006 FIFA World Cup qualification.
